Package edu.umn.biomedicus.tokenization

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Token
    A generic token, extends TextRange has Token.getText containing the covered text and Token.getHasSpaceAfter whether the token has space following it.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DetectParseTokens
    Turns class TokenCandidate labels into class ParseToken labels by using class Sentence labels to split trailing periods.
    DetectTokenCandidates
    Detects class TokenCandidate labels using Tokenizer.
    MergeTermTokens  
    MimicFastTextPreprocessor
    Performs pre-processing on MIMIC tokens before writing them for FastText vector creation.
    MimicFastTextPreprocessorKt  
    ParseToken
    A token roughly equivalent to a penn treebank token. Contains tokens to be labeled with part of speech tags and
    TermToken
    A token which represents a single word or semantic unit. Examples would be the parse tokens "wo" "n't" being merged into "won't".
    TermTokenMerger
    Iterator over a collection of merged tokens. Tokens that are connected by - / \ ' or _ without spaces are merged.
    TokenCandidate
    An initial candidate for tokens. Uses a simple rule based penn-like tokenization without splitting end-of-sentence periods into their own tokens like class ParseToken.
    TokenizationModule  
    WordIndex
    A universal word index (for a word vector space) which is parallel to class ParseToken labels.
